• first open script.sh and have a look.

  • rau_Sept_2_Jan2021 = contains rau dns from sept 2020 to jan 2021

  • rau_2021_02_03 - contains rau dns from 2021 feb and march

  • shankar_2020may_to_202103 = contains videos from another coaching, just to be comprehensive, in case rau wali coaching missed any topic.

In which among the following locations has India established the Strategic Crude oil reserves?

  1. Vishakhapatnam
  2. Mangalore
  3. Mumbai Select the correct answer using the code given below: (a) 1 and 2 only (b) 2 and 3 only (c ) 1 and 3 only (d) 1, 2 and 3

Answer - (a)

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office.
  2. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors.
  3. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP.
  4. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12.
  5. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far.
  6. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs
  7. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India.
  8. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979
  9. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence.
  10. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly.
    Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  11. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office. (True)
  12. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors. (False)
  13. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP. (True)
  14. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12. (True)
  15. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far. (True)
  16. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs. (False)
  17. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India. (True)
  18. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979. (True)
  19. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence. (True)
  20. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly. (True) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-Word ►TODAY’S THE HINDU ANALYSIS

  14. Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle has no utility after the satellites are placed in the orbit. (False)
  15. Agriculture was started in Neolithic period. (True)

  18. Concave lens are used for correction of Myopia. (True)
  19. Remote Sensing Satellites can be used for Telecommunications. (False)
  20. Remote Sensing Satellites can be put in Geostationary orbits. (True)
  21. The RISAT series are the first all-weather Earth Observation Satellites from ISRO. (True)
  22. The reservations provided under Article 16(4) may be called horizontal reservations. (False)
  23. Reservation for women in public employment in the state of Bihar is a form of horizontal reservation. (True)

  1. Maximum of 50% of Total Project Cost can be given by the government as financial help.
  2. The scheme was recommended by Kelkar Committee in 2004.
  3. Niti Aayog is the nodal body for the scheme.
  4. Over the Top (OTT) platforms are considered intermediaries under Section 79 of the IT Act 2000.
  5. OTT platforms will now come under the ambit of Ministry of Information and Broadcasting.
  6. OTT platforms have to get into revenue sharing model with Telcom companies as per the recent government notification.
  7. Advertising Standards Council of India is a self-regulating body.
  8. COVID-19 pandemic has caused the GDP contraction for the first time in last 41 years.
  9. Recession is defined as a fall in the overall economic activity for two consecutive quarters accompanied by a decline in income, sales and employment.
  10. Economic recession is declared by RBI in India as per the RBI act 1934.
  11. An organisation which employs common methods of political action like ‘bandh’ or ‘hartal’, in support of public causes, will be considered as the organisation with political nature under the FCRA act.
  12. Automobiles are covered under Production Linked Incentive scheme. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Maximum of 50% of Total Project Cost can be given by the government as financial help. (False)
  14. The scheme was recommended by Kelkar Committee in 2004. (False)
  15. Niti Aayog is the nodal body for the scheme. (False)
  16. Over the Top (OTT) platforms are considered intermediaries under Section 79 of the IT Act 2000. (True)
  17. OTT platforms will now come under the ambit of Ministry of Information and Broadcasting. (True)
  18. OTT platforms have to get into revenue sharing model with Telcom companies as per the recent government notification. (False)
  19. Advertising Standards Council of India is a self-regulating body. (True)
  20. COVID-19 pandemic has caused the GDP contraction for the first time in last 41 years. (True)
  21. Recession is defined as a fall in the overall economic activity for two consecutive quarters accompanied by a decline in income, sales and employment. (True)
  22. Economic recession is declared by RBI in India as per the RBI act 1934. (False)
  23. An organisation which employs common methods of political action like ‘bandh’ or ‘hartal’, in support of public causes, will be considered as the organisation with political nature under the FCRA act. (False)
  24. Automobiles are covered under Production Linked Incentive scheme. (True) Presented by: Faizan Khan, GS Paper-1 - Answer Key - http://bit.ly/GS-I-Answer-Key-Prelims-2020 y: http://bit.ly/GS-II-CSAT-Ans-Key-2020 DNS

  15. U.S recently has withdrawn from UNHRC, Trans-Pacific Partnership and Global Compact on Migration. (T)
  16. The Srisailam Dam is constructed across the Krishna River. (T)
  17. The delta of river Krishna is one of the most fertile regions in India and was the home to ancient Satavahana and Ikshvaku Sun Dynasty kings. (T)
  18. As the concentration of CO2 is increasing in the atmosphere, food security will be enhanced due to faster growth of cereal crops. (F)

  12. Australia is collaborating with India in development of spacecraft for Gaganyaan Mission. (False)
  13. India has Comprehensive Strategic Partnership with Australia. (True)

  15. Under RCEP agreement, India can keep different rates of tariff for China and other member nations. (True)
  16. The National Statistical Office (NSO) has recently conducted the first Time Use Survey. (True)
  17. One of the sub-goal under SDG 5 is to recognize and value unpaid care and domestic work. (True)
  18. The term ‘radicalisation’ has been defined in Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act. (False)
  19. Kids Right Index is released by UNICEF. (False)

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. Menstruation Benefits Bill was introduced in the parliament by the government in 2017 but is still pending.
  2. Article 42 of the Constitution envisages that the state shall make provision for securing just and humane conditions of work and maternity relief.
  3. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by taking incorrect doses of antibiotics to cure diseases.
  4. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by using antibiotics in livestock farming.
  5. Bihar is the only state in India which has been providing two days of special leave every month to its female employees.
  6. Maternity Benefit Act, 1961 has the provision for Menstruation benefit but has not made it compulsory for the employers.
  7. Female Labour Force Participation Rate (LFPR) is declining despite higher growth, higher educational attainment, and higher age of marriage and declining fertility.
  8. Female LFPR has reduced more in rural areas than in urban areas.
  9. Global Gender Gap Index is released by World Economic Forum.
  10. The NPAs of the PSBs is much higher at around 12% as compared to 9% NPAs in the Banking sector.
  11. P.J. Nayak Committee has recommended merger of weak Banks with the strong Banks.
  12. India’s National Action Plan on Anti-microbial promotes ‘One Health approach’. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Menstruation Benefits Bill was introduced in the parliament by the government in 2017 but is still pending. (False)
  14. Article 42 of the Constitution envisages that the state shall make provision for securing just and humane conditions of work and maternity relief. (True)
  15. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by taking incorrect doses of antibiotics to cure diseases. (True)
  16. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by using antibiotics in livestock farming. (True)
  17. Bihar is the only state in India which has been providing two days of special leave every month to its female employees. (True)
  18. Maternity Benefit Act, 1961 has the provision for Menstruation benefit but has not made it compulsory for the employers. (False)
  19. Female Labour Force Participation Rate (LFPR) is declining despite higher growth, higher educational attainment, and higher age of marriage and declining fertility. (True)
  20. Female LFPR has reduced more in rural areas than in urban areas. (True)
  21. Global Gender Gap Index is released by World Economic Forum. (True)
  22. The NPAs of the PSBs is much higher at around 12% as compared to 9% NPAs in the Banking sector. (True)
  23. P.J. Nayak Committee has recommended merger of weak Banks with the strong Banks. (True)

  1. Justice BN Srikrishna Committee is related to Personal data protection.
  2. In K.S. Puttaswamy vs. Union of India case a nine-judge bench of the Supreme Court of India affirmed the right to privacy as a fundamental right.
  3. The Personal Data Protection Bill 2019 has been tabled in Indian Parliament by the Ministry of Home Affairs.
  4. In Joint parliamentary committee (JPC) Lok Sabha members are double compared to Rajya Sabha.
  5. If a witness fails to appear before a JPC in response to summons, his conduct constitutes a contempt of the House.
  6. Decisions in the JPC are made through simple majority voting, with the Chairperson having a casting vote.
  7. Ministers cannot be called by the committees to give evidence.
  8. Parliamentary privileges are defined in Article 105 of the Indian Constitution
  9. The form of punishments that can be given in case of breach of privilege is provided for by the constitution.
  10. Special Drawing Rights (SDRs) is a form of currency issued by IMF
  11. SDRs are claims of nations on IMF.
  12. If Euro, Pound sterling, Yen gets appreciated against U.S dollar, our Forex reserve will increase.
  13. ‘40+9’ Standards is associated with Financial WTO.
  14. States can amend central laws.
  15. FATF is an arm of OECD. Solution

  17. In K.S. Puttaswamy vs. Union of India case a nine-judge bench of the Supreme Court of India affirmed the right to privacy as a fundamental right. (T)
  18. The Personal Data Protection Bill 2019 has been tabled in Indian Parliament by the Ministry of Home Affairs. (F)
  19. In Joint parliamentary committee (JPC) Lok Sabha members are double compared to Rajya Sabha. (T)
  20. If a witness fails to appear before a JPC in response to summons, his conduct constitutes a contempt of the House. (T)
  21. Decisions in the JPC are made through simple majority voting, with the Chairperson having a casting vote. (T)
  22. Ministers cannot be called by the committees to give evidence. (F)
  23. Parliamentary privileges are defined in Article 105 of the Indian Constitution. (T)
  24. The form of punishments that can be given in case of breach of privilege is provided for by the constitution. (F)
  25. Special Drawing Rights (SDRs) is a form of currency issued by IMF. (F)
  26. SDRs are claims of nations on IMF. (F)
  27. If Euro, Pound sterling, Yen gets appreciated against U.S dollar, our Forex reserve will increase. (T)
  28. ‘40+9’ Standards is associated with Financial WTO. (F)

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. Electricity has the highest weight in the Index of Eight Core Industries
  2. State of Food Security and Nutrition in the World 2020 has been released by Food and Agricultural Organisation
  3. Domestic currency may weaken as a result of large fiscal deficit.
  4. Lingayats oppose cremation and follow burial rituals.
  5. Lingayat is a Shaivite sect following the philosophy of Dvaita.
  6. Effective revenue deficit is revenue deficit minus the expenditure on the creation of capital assets.
  7. If a primary deficit of a country is shrinking it means fiscal health of economy is improving.
  8. As per the Section 4(2) of the FRBM Act 2003, the Centre can exceed the annual fiscal deficit target citing certain grounds. Collapse of agriculture is one of the grounds.
  9. ILO Declaration of Philadelphia, 1944 states “Poverty anywhere is a threat to prosperity everywhere.”
  10. “Hunger Watch” is a speed survey started by the Right to Food Campaign
  11. As per article 48 of the constitution, it is the duty of the State to raise the level of nutrition and the standard of living and to improve public health
  12. Index of industrial production is prepared by CSO. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Electricity has the highest weight in the Index of Eight Core Industries. (False)
  14. State of Food Security and Nutrition in the World 2020 has been released by Food and Agricultural Organisation. (True)
  15. Domestic currency may weaken as a result of large fiscal deficit. (True)
  16. Lingayats oppose cremation and follow burial rituals. (True)
  17. Lingayat is a Shaivite sect following the philosophy of Dvaita. (False)
  18. Effective revenue deficit is revenue deficit minus the expenditure on the creation of capital assets. (False)
  19. If a primary deficit of a country is shrinking it means fiscal health of economy is improving. (True)
  20. As per the Section 4(2) of the FRBM Act 2003, the Centre can exceed the annual fiscal deficit target citing certain grounds. Collapse of agriculture is one of the grounds. (True)
  21. ILO Declaration of Philadelphia, 1944 states “Poverty anywhere is a threat to prosperity everywhere.” (True)
  22. “Hunger Watch” is a speed survey started by the Right to Food Campaign. (True)
  23. As per article 48 of the constitution, it is the duty of the State to raise the level of nutrition and the standard of living and to improve public health. (False)
  24. Index of industrial production is prepared by CSO. (False) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-NOTES-28-11-20_PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-NOTES-28-11-20-WORD ►TODAY’S THE HINDU ANALYSIS

Presented by: Faizan Khan, Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office.
  2. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors.
  3. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP.
  4. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12.
  5. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far.
  6. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs
  7. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India.
  8. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979
  9. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence.
  10. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly.
    Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  11. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office. (True)
  12. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors. (False)
  13. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP. (True)
  14. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12. (True)
  15. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far. (True)
  16. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs. (False)
  17. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India. (True)
  18. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979. (True)
  19. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence. (True)
  20. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly. (True) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-Word

  17. The delta of river Krishna is one of the most fertile regions in India and was the home to ancient Satavahana and Ikshvaku Sun Dynasty kings. (T)
  18. As the concentration of CO2 is increasing in the atmosphere, food security will be enhanced due to faster growth of cereal crops. (F)

Shankar IAS Academy is launching a free online initiative in YouTube for the benefit of Civil Service Aspirants. A programme on International Relations wherein we will post one class a week as a weekly capsule. The sessions will be explained by former Indian Foreign Service officer Shri T P Sreenivasan. Step 2: Upload the PDF file in your google drive. Step 3: Right click on the file and choose 'Get shareable link', then, click 'sharing settings'. Step 4: Click 'Advanced' and change the 'specific people to access' setting to 'Anyone with the link can view'. Step 5. Save the changed setting and copy the link. Step 6: Paste the link in the comment section.

Shankar IAS Academy is launching a free online initiative in YouTube for the benefit of Civil Service Aspirants. A programme on International Relations wherein we will post one class a week as a weekly capsule. The sessions will be explained by former Indian Foreign Service officer Shri T P Sreenivasan. He is a former ambassador of India and a former Permanent Representative of India to the United Nations, Vienna. He has served in the Indian Foreign Service for 37 years. He has also served as the Governor for India at the International Atomic Energy Agency. He is also a former member of National Security Advisory Board of Government of India. Capsule I of the series was published on 14th January 2021, on the Shankar IAS Academy YouTube Channel.

Answer to Yesterdays Question of the Day is option (a)

In which among the following locations has India established the Strategic Crude oil reserves?

  1. Vishakhapatnam
  2. Mangalore
  3. Mumbai Select the correct answer using the code given below: (a) 1 and 2 only (b) 2 and 3 only (c ) 1 and 3 only (d) 1, 2 and 3

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office.
  2. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors.
  3. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP.
  4. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12.
  5. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far.
  6. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs
  7. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India.
  8. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979
  9. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence.
  10. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly.
    Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  11. GDP estimation in India is done by Central Statistics Office. (True)
  12. The GDP estimates are based upon the direct measurement of economic activity in both Organized and Unorganized Sectors. (False)
  13. MCA-21 is used for estimating both the national level as well as state level GDP. (True)
  14. The base year for the calculation of the GDP is 2011-12. (True)
  15. The caste portion of the Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) 2011 has not been disclosed so far. (True)
  16. SECC was commenced by Ministry of Home Affairs. (False)
  17. Justice Fathima Beevi was the first female judge of the Supreme Court of India. (True)
  18. India is a signatory to Conventions on Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW), 1979. (True)
  19. Violating the rights of the Legislative Assembly can attract Jail sentence. (True)
  20. A CAG report has to remain a confidential document till it is tabled in the Legislative Assembly. (True) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-03-12-20-Word ►TODAY’S THE HINDU ANALYSIS

  1. Maximum of 50% of Total Project Cost can be given by the government as financial help.
  2. The scheme was recommended by Kelkar Committee in 2004.
  3. Niti Aayog is the nodal body for the scheme.
  4. Over the Top (OTT) platforms are considered intermediaries under Section 79 of the IT Act 2000.
  5. OTT platforms will now come under the ambit of Ministry of Information and Broadcasting.
  6. OTT platforms have to get into revenue sharing model with Telcom companies as per the recent government notification.
  7. Advertising Standards Council of India is a self-regulating body.
  8. COVID-19 pandemic has caused the GDP contraction for the first time in last 41 years.
  9. Recession is defined as a fall in the overall economic activity for two consecutive quarters accompanied by a decline in income, sales and employment.
  10. Economic recession is declared by RBI in India as per the RBI act 1934.
  11. An organisation which employs common methods of political action like ‘bandh’ or ‘hartal’, in support of public causes, will be considered as the organisation with political nature under the FCRA act.
  12. Automobiles are covered under Production Linked Incentive scheme. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Maximum of 50% of Total Project Cost can be given by the government as financial help. (False)
  14. The scheme was recommended by Kelkar Committee in 2004. (False)
  15. Niti Aayog is the nodal body for the scheme. (False)
  16. Over the Top (OTT) platforms are considered intermediaries under Section 79 of the IT Act 2000. (True)
  17. OTT platforms will now come under the ambit of Ministry of Information and Broadcasting. (True)
  18. OTT platforms have to get into revenue sharing model with Telcom companies as per the recent government notification. (False)
  19. Advertising Standards Council of India is a self-regulating body. (True)
  20. COVID-19 pandemic has caused the GDP contraction for the first time in last 41 years. (True)
  21. Recession is defined as a fall in the overall economic activity for two consecutive quarters accompanied by a decline in income, sales and employment. (True)
  22. Economic recession is declared by RBI in India as per the RBI act 1934. (False)
  23. An organisation which employs common methods of political action like ‘bandh’ or ‘hartal’, in support of public causes, will be considered as the organisation with political nature under the FCRA act. (False)
  24. Automobiles are covered under Production Linked Incentive scheme. (True) Presented by: Faizan Khan, GS Paper-1 - Answer Key - http://bit.ly/GS-I-Answer-Key-Prelims-2020 y: http://bit.ly/GS-II-CSAT-Ans-Key-2020 DNS

  1. UN Human Rights Council is a treaty based organisation.
  2. UNHRC passes non-binding resolutions on human rights issues.
  3. Human Rights Committee and the Committee on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights works as attached body of UNHRC.
  4. Universal Periodic Review mechanism is associated with IMF.
  5. U.S recently has withdrawn from UNHRC, Trans-Pacific Partnership and Global Compact on Migration.
  6. The Srisailam Dam is constructed across the Krishna River.
  7. The delta of river Krishna is one of the most fertile regions in India and was the home to ancient Satavahana and Ikshvaku Sun Dynasty kings.
  8. As the concentration of CO2 is increasing in the atmosphere, food security will be enhanced due to faster growth of cereal crops.
  9. The ‘In-house procedure’ of Supreme Court, for complaints against judges, started in the aftermath of the emergency.
  10. Increased CO2 in the atmosphere at the same time restricts plant’s ability to absorb nitrogen. Solution
  11. UN Human Rights Council is a treaty based organisation. (F)
  12. UNHRC passes non-binding resolutions on human rights issues. (T)

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. Menstruation Benefits Bill was introduced in the parliament by the government in 2017 but is still pending.
  2. Article 42 of the Constitution envisages that the state shall make provision for securing just and humane conditions of work and maternity relief.
  3. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by taking incorrect doses of antibiotics to cure diseases.
  4. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by using antibiotics in livestock farming.
  5. Bihar is the only state in India which has been providing two days of special leave every month to its female employees.
  6. Maternity Benefit Act, 1961 has the provision for Menstruation benefit but has not made it compulsory for the employers.
  7. Female Labour Force Participation Rate (LFPR) is declining despite higher growth, higher educational attainment, and higher age of marriage and declining fertility.
  8. Female LFPR has reduced more in rural areas than in urban areas.
  9. Global Gender Gap Index is released by World Economic Forum.
  10. The NPAs of the PSBs is much higher at around 12% as compared to 9% NPAs in the Banking sector.
  11. P.J. Nayak Committee has recommended merger of weak Banks with the strong Banks.
  12. India’s National Action Plan on Anti-microbial promotes ‘One Health approach’. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Menstruation Benefits Bill was introduced in the parliament by the government in 2017 but is still pending. (False)
  14. Article 42 of the Constitution envisages that the state shall make provision for securing just and humane conditions of work and maternity relief. (True)
  15. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by taking incorrect doses of antibiotics to cure diseases. (True)
  16. Multi-drug resistance in microbial pathogens may be caused by using antibiotics in livestock farming. (True)
  17. Bihar is the only state in India which has been providing two days of special leave every month to its female employees. (True)
  18. Maternity Benefit Act, 1961 has the provision for Menstruation benefit but has not made it compulsory for the employers. (False)
  19. Female Labour Force Participation Rate (LFPR) is declining despite higher growth, higher educational attainment, and higher age of marriage and declining fertility. (True)
  20. Female LFPR has reduced more in rural areas than in urban areas. (True)
  21. Global Gender Gap Index is released by World Economic Forum. (True)
  22. The NPAs of the PSBs is much higher at around 12% as compared to 9% NPAs in the Banking sector. (True)
  23. P.J. Nayak Committee has recommended merger of weak Banks with the strong Banks. (True)
  24. India’s National Action Plan on Anti-microbial promotes ‘One Health approach’. (True) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-24-11-20-PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-24-11-20-Word ►TODAY’S THE HINDU ANALYSIS

  1. Justice BN Srikrishna Committee is related to Personal data protection.

  17. In K.S. Puttaswamy vs. Union of India case a nine-judge bench of the Supreme Court of India affirmed the right to privacy as a fundamental right. (T)

  20. If a witness fails to appear before a JPC in response to summons, his conduct constitutes a contempt of the House. (T)
  21. Decisions in the JPC are made through simple majority voting, with the Chairperson having a casting vote. (T)

Self-Assessment Speed Test

  1. Electricity has the highest weight in the Index of Eight Core Industries
  2. State of Food Security and Nutrition in the World 2020 has been released by Food and Agricultural Organisation
  3. Domestic currency may weaken as a result of large fiscal deficit.
  4. Lingayats oppose cremation and follow burial rituals.
  5. Lingayat is a Shaivite sect following the philosophy of Dvaita.
  6. Effective revenue deficit is revenue deficit minus the expenditure on the creation of capital assets.
  7. If a primary deficit of a country is shrinking it means fiscal health of economy is improving.
  8. As per the Section 4(2) of the FRBM Act 2003, the Centre can exceed the annual fiscal deficit target citing certain grounds. Collapse of agriculture is one of the grounds.
  9. ILO Declaration of Philadelphia, 1944 states “Poverty anywhere is a threat to prosperity everywhere.”
  10. “Hunger Watch” is a speed survey started by the Right to Food Campaign
  11. As per article 48 of the constitution, it is the duty of the State to raise the level of nutrition and the standard of living and to improve public health
  12. Index of industrial production is prepared by CSO. Self-Assessment Speed Test (Solution)
  13. Electricity has the highest weight in the Index of Eight Core Industries. (False)
  14. State of Food Security and Nutrition in the World 2020 has been released by Food and Agricultural Organisation. (True)
  15. Domestic currency may weaken as a result of large fiscal deficit. (True)
  16. Lingayats oppose cremation and follow burial rituals. (True)
  17. Lingayat is a Shaivite sect following the philosophy of Dvaita. (False)
  18. Effective revenue deficit is revenue deficit minus the expenditure on the creation of capital assets. (False)
  19. If a primary deficit of a country is shrinking it means fiscal health of economy is improving. (True)
  20. As per the Section 4(2) of the FRBM Act 2003, the Centre can exceed the annual fiscal deficit target citing certain grounds. Collapse of agriculture is one of the grounds. (True)
  21. ILO Declaration of Philadelphia, 1944 states “Poverty anywhere is a threat to prosperity everywhere.” (True)
  22. “Hunger Watch” is a speed survey started by the Right to Food Campaign. (True)
  23. As per article 48 of the constitution, it is the duty of the State to raise the level of nutrition and the standard of living and to improve public health. (False)
  24. Index of industrial production is prepared by CSO. (False) PDF - https://bit.ly/DNS-NOTES-28-11-20_PDF Word - https://bit.ly/DNS-NOTES-28-11-20-WORD ►TODAY’S THE HINDU ANALYSIS
  25. Prelims Test Series Course announcement - (00:15)
  26. Stepping out of the shadow of India’s malnutrition - (Indian Society + Polity & Governance + Indian Economy ) - (03:36) (Nutrition and Health)

PDF Link: http://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-18-10-20-PDF Word Link: http://bit.ly/DNS-Notes-18-10-20-Word Self Assessment Speed Test

  1. UN Human Rights Council is a treaty based organisation.
  2. UNHRC passes non-binding resolutions on human rights issues.
  3. Human Rights Committee and the Committee on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights works as attached body of UNHRC.
  4. Universal Periodic Review mechanism is associated with IMF.
  5. U.S recently has withdrawn from UNHRC, Trans-Pacific Partnership and Global Compact on Migration.
  6. The Srisailam Dam is constructed across the Krishna River.
  7. The delta of river Krishna is one of the most fertile regions in India and was the home to ancient Satavahana and Ikshvaku Sun Dynasty kings.
  8. As the concentration of CO2 is increasing in the atmosphere, food security will be enhanced due to faster growth of cereal crops.
  9. The ‘In-house procedure’ of Supreme Court, for complaints against judges, started in the aftermath of the emergency.
  10. Increased CO2 in the atmosphere at the same time restricts plant’s ability to absorb nitrogen. Solution
  11. UN Human Rights Council is a treaty based organisation. (F)
  12. UNHRC passes non-binding resolutions on human rights issues. (T)
  13. Human Rights Committee and the Committee on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights works as attached body of UNHRC. (F)
  14. Universal Periodic Review mechanism is associated with IMF. (F)
  15. U.S recently has withdrawn from UNHRC, Trans-Pacific Partnership and Global Compact on Migration. (T)
  16. The Srisailam Dam is constructed across the Krishna River. (T)
  17. The delta of river Krishna is one of the most fertile regions in India and was the home to ancient Satavahana and Ikshvaku Sun Dynasty kings. (T)
  18. As the concentration of CO2 is increasing in the atmosphere, food security will be enhanced due to faster growth of cereal crops. (F)
  19. The ‘In-house procedure’ of Supreme Court, for complaints against judges, started in the aftermath of the emergency. (F)
  20. Increased CO2 in the atmosphere at the same time restricts plant’s ability to absorb nitrogen. (T)
  21. Announcement of the release of Mains Compass of Ethics, Integrity and Aptitude (00:15)

Step 2: Upload the PDF file in your google drive. Step 3: Right click on the file and choose 'Get shareable link', then, click 'sharing settings'. Step 4: Click 'Advanced' and change the 'specific people to access' setting to 'Anyone with the link can view'. Step 5. Save the changed setting and copy the link. Step 6: Paste the link in the comment section.
